name: Bitterling
description: This fish has a reputation for tasting bitter, experienced cooks know how to prepare it in ways that are quite delicious.

name: Popeye Goldfish
description: This fish's crazy eyes gives it excellent vision, making it great at spotting prey- or your hook!

name: Clown Fish
description: Tell us a joke, clown fish. ...Oh wait, fish can't talk.

name: Black Bass
description: Caught for sport in many areas of the world, many new anglers are excited to catch this fish for the first time.

name: Salmon
description: Commonly found in rivers, though this fish is no stranger to lakes, ponds, oceans, extra big puddles, etc...

name: Tiger Trout
description: This fish uses its striped coloration to stalk between underwater reeds, much as a tiger does. Hence the name.

name: Tuna
description: So-called "chicken of the sea", but where are it's feathers?!

name: Lobster
description: A Sun Haven favorite, townies are especially fond of drenching these guys in plenty of fresh butter.

name: Ribbon Eel
description: An impossibly thin eel, its physiology confounds scholars even to this day.

name: Koi Fish
description: A fish brought to this part of the world from a far away continent, they can grow quite large when they have enough space and food.

name: Bomb Fish
description: It's like any other regular, normal fish... except it explodes!!

name: Rock Bass
description: This bass is as dense as a rock! It that packed on the pounds for a long winter.

name: Northern Pike
description: The icy waters of the Northern Region aren't an easy place to get by. Migrating south for the winter is one way to find enough food for the winter.

name: Frostfin
description: An frozen fish that prefers to blend in with the winter crowd.

name: Christmas Lightfish
description: People of the Southern Isles have the oddest tradition of topping their holiday trees with this festive fish.

name: Holly Carp
description: Deck the halls with fish of holly, fa la la la...

name: Jingle Bass
description: It jingles just like a bell! It also LOOKS just like a bell...

name: Frozen Tuna
description: Not every fish deals with winter so well.

name: Scarffish
description: It looks warm and fuzzy, but it's actually wet and slimy. Sorry.

name: Heatfin
description: A beautiful flaming fish, its bright orange color sets it apart from your typical winter species.

name: Icicle Carp
description: A lazy carp that moves so slowly it can sometimes be found with icicles hanging from its fins!

name: Blazing Herring
description: This herring is a lightning fast swimmer, keeping its body running warm even in the cold of winter.

name: Coalfish
description: Tastes considerably better than its namesake, thankfully.

name: Blazeel
description: Though native to the Magma Isles, this eel can be found as far north as Sun Haven when the weather is hot enough.

name: Inferno Guppy
description: Small, but spicy!

name: Hearth Angler
description: Its lure light not only draws prey in, but also helps cook it to a delicious crisp.

name: Scorching Squid
description: A migrant squid from the distant Magma Isles, a chain of ashy islands constantly being broken and reformed by underwater volcanic activity.

name: Magma Star
description: Far past the Southern Isles lay the Magma Isles, inhospitable to any life that can't tolerate a bit of molten lava... like this little starfish!

name: Tinder Turtle
description: There's nothing tender about a sea turtle who has a molten volcano for a shell.

name: Pyrelus
description: Native to the Magma Isles, this nautilus migrates north in the summer season to search for fresh prey.

name: Flame Ray
description: A ray that looks just like a flying fireball as it glides through the waves.

name: Molten Slug
description: Researchers would love to know more about the aquatic species that live in the Magma Isles, though traveling there is nearly impossible.

name: Searback
description: Its dorsal fins are on fire - literally! Hmm, it reminds you of a fire Elemental...

name: Flower Flounder
description: Researchers claim this fish's unique body structure helps it survive in the wild. Well, if they say so...

name: Blooming Bass
description: This clever bass uses freshly bloomed water lilies to lure in its insect prey.

name: Sunfish
description: This grouper prefers to swim at the water's surface, allowing its shimmery scales to catch the light of the sun.

name: Butterflyfish
description: Did it come from a sea cocoon?

name: Raincloud Ray
description: A popular fisherman's myth is that this ray is easiest to catch during rainstorms.

name: Floral Trout
description: The pattern of this trout's scales are uncannily similar to a floral pattern, hence the name.

name: Mud Catfish
description: A fat, lazy catfish that prefers to spend its time suctioned in sand and mud, waiting for prey to pass by.

name: Neon Tetra
description: A bold tetra fish whose striking neon colors pose not as a warning to potential predators - but a challenge!

name: Seahorse
description: Looks like a little small to ride, sadly.

name: Painted Egg
description: Can we offer you an egg in these trying times?

name: Tadpole
description: Just a tad lad.

name: Coducopia
description: Hey, this would look great in a cornucopia.

name: King Salmon
description: Please unhook his royal highness, ye base and most uncouth farmer.

name: Hayfish
description: Hay is for horses. And apparently fish.

name: Acorn Anchovy
description: Perhaps the world's least favorite pizza topping.

name: Turkeyfish
description: Gobble gobble? More like glubble glubble.

name: Trick or Trout
description: You'd rather not find it in your trick or treat bag.

name: Vampire Piranha
description: So named for its dark red belly and thankfully not for any blood sucking tendencies!

name: Ghostfish
description: A harmless jellyfish that is totally invisible in the water. All the same, however, fishermen consider this spooky jelly to be a sign of bad luck.

name: Pumpkin Jelly
description: Careful, its tentacles can leave a nasty sting... though it does go great in a pie.

name: Pirate Perch
description: Though this fish looks tough and grizzled, actually they argghhh quite tasty.

name: Autumn Leaf Sole
description: This fish experiences a physical transformation in the fall season, blending in with falling leaves.

name: Bone Gift
description: A great gift for unusual friends!

name: Apple Cider
description: Ripe apples, pressed into a pulpy juice and spiced to cidery perfection.

name: Strawberry Milk
description: Milk... from a strawberry? Nah, just strawberry flavored cow milk!

name: Blueberry Muffin
description: A perfectly baked muffin dotted with juicy little blueberries.

name: Fruit Punch
description: A tropical drink that originated in the sunny Southern Islands, it's become a staple drink at parties and celebrations.

name: Raspberry Crepes
description: A crepe is like a fancy little pancake, filled with sweet raspberries it makes an extra yummy treat.

name: Fruit Tart
description: Aptly named, this pastry has a sharp tart kick in contrast to the sweet fruit and sugary crust.

name: Linguine with Clams
description: Thick sauce and noodles served with steamed clams, a great choice for a filling seafood meal.

name: Peaches and Cream
description: Sliced peaches served in a creamed milk sauce. This is sometimes used as the filling for a pie but it's just as good on its own.

name: Tikka Masala
description: Seared vegetables in a searingly spicy sauce, it's quite delicious if you can make it past the heat.

name: California Roll
description: A type of sushi roll native to a far, far away and mythical land that is only spoken about in legends.

name: Fish Taco
description: A little different from what most people think of when it comes to "tacos", but still very delicious.

name: Creamy Mushroom Soup
description: In the past this simple soup was made due to a lack for any better ingredients. Today, however, it's an old fashioned comfort food classic.

name: Waffles
description: Light and airy on the inside, but golden and crunchy on the outside. All that's missing is a slab of butter and a bucket of syrup.

name: Nachos
description: If they're nacho chips, then who's are they? They're mine!

name: Lobster Roll
description: Seasoned lobster meat, served in a hotdog bun of all things. A bit strange, but it totally works.

name: Pad Thai
description: Stir-fried noodles and nuts, this is served as a popular street food in cities all over the four regions.

name: Lasagna
description: A classic dish from the Eastern Region, layers of sauce and noodles that make for a hearty dinner meal.

name: Potato Salad
description: A gooey mixture of potatoes and egg, it's not like any salad you've ever heard of before but it's pretty tasty.

name: Ice Cream
description: It's just milk and honey churned in ice, but it's irresistably delicious.

name: Yogurt Parfait
description: Yogurt and strawberries, layered together and topped with honeyed oats. Unbeatable when it comes to being quick, simple and delicious.

name: Omelet
description: A basic egg dish, great for breakfast. Or lunch. Or dinner. Or whenever!

name: Fish and Chips
description: Deep fried fish served with a side of chips, can you believe some people actually call them "fries"?!

name: Lobster Bisque
description: Soft chunks of delicate lobster meat, swimming in a thick and creamy soup.

name: Grilled Cheese
description: Many a beginner chef's first dish, its simplicity does not subtract from its yummyness.

name: Onion Rings
description: Onion slices, breaded and fried in oil. Vegetables don't taste better than this.

name: Sweet and Spicy Shrimp
description: Sweetness and spiciness battle each other for dominance in this shrimp dish. The winner of their duel? Your tastebuds.

name: Seafood Gumbo
description: A thin stew of assorted crustaceans, its spice and heat perfectly accent the tender seafood.

name: Poke Bowl
description: Seasoned fish served over rice, simple fare often enjoyed by sailors while out at sea.

name: Apple Sauce
description: A soft 'sauce' of mashed apples, easy to make and even easier to eat.

name: Veggie Kebab
description: Skewered veggies roasted over an open flame, the crisp taste of the fire adds a remarkably complex taste to the veggies.

name: Strawberry Shortcake
description: Some people enjoy letting the juice of the strawberry soak into the shortcake, while others try to eat it before that can happen.

name: Mochi Covered Strawberry
description: A strawberry, covered in a thin layer of flavored mochi. A lightweight but lovely dessert.

name: Acai Bowl
description: Sweet yogurt topped with an assortment of berries, a common breakfast food for many across the land.

name: Citrus Salad
description: Fragrant and slightly tangy, it's very invigorating for only being a 'mere' salad.

name: Fruit Snacks
description: Squishly little fruit snacks, an even more fun way to eat your fruits.

name: Tuna Nigiri
description: Raw fish can taste good? Who would have thought.

name: Tortilla Chips
description: A corn tortilla, cut up and turned into delicious crunchy chips thanks to the magic of deep frying.

name: Salsa
description: A loose sauce of tomato and spices, its zesty zing certainly dresses up all sorts of dishes.

name: Mushroom Risotto
description: Labor intensive to prepare, but the savory mushroom mixed with the twice-cooked rice is an excellent reward for the effort.

name: Mochi
description: Sweetened rice paste, shaped into a spongey cake and steamed before baking.

name: Mushroom Stroganoff
description: Roast mushrooms, drenched in a thick and savory broth. A peasant meal, but still fit for a king.

name: Veggie Wrap
description: Diced veggies wrapped in a corn tortilla, the soft wrap contrasts well against the crunchy vegetables inside.

name: Trail Mix
description: A mix of energy-boosting food to keep one fueled over long adventures.

name: Churros
description: Dough sticks, fried in oil and breaded with sugar. Simple, yet very delicious.

name: Tortilla
description: A corn tortilla made of corn flour dough and baked over an open fire, it's like bread only... super flat.

name: Corn Flour
description: Made of finely milled corn. It's heavier than wheat flour and slightly sweeter, too.

name: Hydrangea Cupcake
description: A cupcake topped with an intricately piped frosting design, world famous pastry chef Ramiro is credited for inventing this style of frosting.

name: Chicken Bastilla
description: Shredded chicken wrapped in layers of paper-thin dough. This delicious pastry was the signature dish of Raine, a world-famous chef and culinary visionary.

name: Sombasu's Fortune #1
description:
A great opportunity for love will present itself to you, but it will rely on you grabbing it...
...Your lucky numbers are 9, 37, 78...

name: Sombasu's Fortune #2
description:
You will befriend many animals to fill your stables, but beware... of the clean-up...
...Your lucky numbers are 4, 33,17...

name: Sombasu's Fortune #3
description:
A sizable fortune is waiting to be delivered to you, but the sender doesn't have a stamp to mail it...
...Your lucky numbers are 66, 23, 1...

name: Sombasu's Fortune #4
description:
Somewhere out there, a Snaccoon is waiting for you to feed it...
...Your lucky numbers are 83, 21, 67...

name: Sombasu's Fortune #5
description:
Come next dawn, you shall feel compelled to water any crops you are growing...
...Your lucky numbers are 17, 41, 36...

name: Sombasu's Fortune #6
description:
You will be blessed with immense fame and adoration from all stretches of the world... on the next sunny day in Withergate...
...Your lucky numbers are 12, 25, 14...

name: Sombasu's Fortune #7
description:
You will suddenly become horrifyingly aware that you have not bathed since arriving in Sun Haven...
...Your lucky numbers are 8, 3, 13...

name: Sombasu's Fortune #8
description:
You will feel compelled to sleep tonight by exactly midnight...
...Your lucky numbers are 2, 77, 32...

name: Sombasu's Fortune #9
description:
I see... farming... somewhere in your future...
...Your lucky numbers are 14, 37, 4...

name: Sombasu's Fortune #10
description:
You will own many outfits... but never change your underwear...
...Your lucky numbers are 7, 13, 18...

name: Sombasu's Fortune #11
description:
The spirits tell me... Sun Haven's General Store shall open for business at precisely 8 a.m. tomorrow...
...Your lucky numbers are 11, 24, 55...

name: Sombasu's Fortune #12
description:
The next time you cut down a tree, you shall find logs...
...Your lucky numbers are 16, 33, 56...

name: Sombasu's Fortune #13
description:
I hear two spirits... one tells me the next time you go fishing, you shall catch nothing. The other tells me that the next time you go fishing, you shall indeed catch a fish...
...The spirits won't come to an agreeance... that's just how it is sometimes...
...Your lucky numbers are 74, 5, 23...

name: Sombasu's Fortune #14
description:
When next you place items in your Shipping Portal, you shall receive a bounty of coins...
...Your lucky numbers are 25, 74, 38...

name: Sombasu's Fortune #15
description:
I see... in the distant future... the one called "Emmett"... still... in debt...
...Your lucky numbers are 63, 37, 19...

name: Sombasu's Fortune #16
description:
You will wonder what your lucky numbers mean...
...Your lucky numbers are 4, 21, 48...

name: Sombasu's Fortune #17
description:
I see you, walking on the beach... your feet get covered in sand. It is coarse and rough, irritating... and gets everywhere...
...Your lucky numbers are 16, 9, 71...

name: Dragonfly

name: Haunted Log
description: A log, haunted by the restless soul of a vengeful stump.

name: Hot Sauce
description: A Scorpepper's sting is searingly hot, owed all to heat of their saucey venom. Silver lining? It's the ultimate meal enhancer.

name: Ice Cube
description: A terribly cold cube of ice, it doesn't melt even on the hottest day.

name: Orange Pepper Flakes
description: Dried peppers, crushed into flakes. The drying process made these peppers extra spicy!

name: Soot
description: Smoldering ash, it's still rather hot to the touch.

description: Some people use this ultra-sticky sap as a glue, owing to the fact it sticks almost anything together fairly permanently.

name: Snow Ball
description: Packed so extremely tight that it feels more like a rock than snow.

name: Lava Honey
description: Sweet like delicious honey... and hot like molten lava...

name: Pricklepop Pear
description: A sour pear covered in pointy thorns, no good for eating.

name: Dandelion

name: Lynn's Pickaxe
description: Lynn's trusty pickaxe. Looks like Solon has taken good care of it.

name: Fly
description: Flies are pretty gross, but it's said that frogs will gift them to those who are worthy. Worthy of what, though?

name: Sludge
description: A handful of gross sewer muck, it seems some lingering magical force had inadvertently enchanted it into a rampaging monster.

name: Cardboard Box Piece
description: A piece of cardboard. With enough of these, maybe you could create something incredible?

name: Bent Traffic Cone

name: Tough Tin Can
description: Monster trash from the streets above, it seems as if the citizens of Withergate aren't ones for recycling.

name: Tough Trash Bag
description: An empty trash bag from the streets above, it's extra tough and not a bad home for a crab.

name: Sand
description: Normal castles are built of stone and wood, but legendary castles are built from sand.

name: Croc Scale
description: Long ago the untamed swamps of Withergate were home to vicious crocodiles. Though the Demons have since made their city on the land, the crocs have adapted to sewer life fairly well.

name: Slime Goop

name: Petrified Log
description:
A log of strange, stoney wood. Scholars would love to study this.
It would look good in a museum!

name: Phoenix Feather
description:
A wispy feather of a mystical pheonix, sometimes known as 'dragon birds'.
It would look good in a museum!

name: Fairy Wings
description:
Fairies are thought to be related to the Elves. Beings of pure mana, their wings are left behind whenever they disperse into energy.
It would look good in a museum!

name: Griffon Egg
description:
A fossilized griffon egg. This proves that griffons have lived in this area for a very long time.
It would look good in a museum!

name: Mana Sap
description:
Tree sap, dense with mana energy. Very much worth studying.
It would look good in a museum!

name: Pumice Stone
description:
Pumice is left behind by volcanic activity. Where in these lands are there volcanos?!
It would look good in a museum!

name: Mysterious Antler
description:
A strange antler. It looks quite old, and it doesn't look like it came from any sort of deer or hornsnake.
It would look good in a museum!

name: Dragon Fang
description:
The fang of an immature dragon, likely intentionally shed from the mouth to make way for big boy dragon teeth.
It would look good in a museum!

name: Monster Candy
description:
A piece of Monsterfolk candy, some scholars believe the Monsterfolk race trade candy as a form of currency.
It would look good in a museum!

name: Unicorn Hair Tuft
description:
Roughly 1% of a unicorn. It must have been lost as the magical beast galloped through the woods.
It would look good in a museum!

name: Handmade Bobber
description:
A well used fishing bobber, hand crafted in the ancient style of the Southern Isles fishermen.
It would look good in a museum!

name: Ancient Magic Staff
description:
Lost for unknown ages, this staff still radiates the faintest signature of magic energy.
It would look good in a museum!

name: Bronze Dragon Relic
description:
It's a bronze dragon, countless years have worn away its features but you'd wager it looks a bit like Elios...
It would look good in a museum!

name: Old Sword Hilt
description:
An old sword hilt, the crossguard bears an unknown crest.
It would look good in a museum!

name: Nel'Varian Runestone
description:
A stone carved with delicate Nel'Varian runes. It repels your touch ever so slightly.
It would look good in a museum!

name: Ancient Elven Headdress
description:
Despite its age, the headdress has preserved nicely. Maybe it was meant for some sort of old Elven celebration?
It would look good in a museum!

name: Old Mayoral Painting
description:
It's a portrait of an old well dressed gentleman. On the breast of his coat is the Sun Haven emblem... was this a past town leader?
It would look good in a museum!

name: Tentacle Monster Emblem
description:
This emblem is carved of a strange stone, depicting a bizarre alien beast. The words 'Cw'thlza, xx'frer'tiz O'aj'loza!' are carved into the emblem's backside.
It would look good in a museum!

name: Ancient Angel Quill
description:
A writing quill, it appears to be of Angelic origin. It has to be eons old, yet the ink on its tip is still wet.
It would look good in a museum!

name: Ancient Naga Crook
description:
A serpentine shepherd crook. If you had to hazard a guess, you would say it looks Naga in origin.
It would look good in a museum!

name: Ancient Amari Totem
description:
An old totem seemingly dedicated to the ferocity of nature. Could it be Amari in origin?
It would look good in a museum!

name: Ancient Sun Haven Sword
description:
A chipped sword, bearing the colors of Elios. It's quite old, and seems to be ceremonial rather than for combat use.
It would look good in a museum!

name: Ancient Nel'Varian Sword
description:
A metal blade, clearly Nel'Varian in origin. It's very old, and it looks like it's seen use in combat...
It would look good in a museum!

name: Ancient Withergate Sword
description:
A wicked Demon blade, left to rust and degrade in the dirt. It seems old, and has clearly seen much use in war.
It would look good in a museum!

name: Community Token
description: A token proving your contribution to Sun Haven's community. Bernard will trade these for all sorts of amazing things at Town Hall.

name: Darkness Essence
description: A thick droplet of darkness energy. It feels strangely similar to mana, but... somehow twisted and wrong.

name: Mana Shard
description:
A shard of twinkling mana, shed by the Great Tree of Nel'Vari. The members of the Restoration Society would be very interested in this.
"There's memory in mana, the energy that fuels all life." - Nivara

name: Candy Corn Pieces
description: Used as a currency by monsterfolk, accepted at the shops in the Withergate subway. Do you think they grow it on candy farms?

name: Kingly Ticket
description:
A ticket permitting one ride on the Withergate subway train. This kingly ticket is more likely to take you to a large neighborhood.

"We'll just charge a TICKET for the subway! Tickets are the solution to everything! Bwhaha!" - Xyla

name: Ladybug Plushie
description: This is one ladybug that can fly away home... to join your plushie collection!

name: Apple and Worm Plushie
description: This plushie would make a great gag gift for a teacher, or anyone else who loves a little worm in their life.

name: Cobra Plushie
description: A venomous snake from far away lands... so of course Demons turned it into a cute plushie.

name: Snail Plushie
description: Monster children all across Withergate city are known for snuggling up in bed each night with their teddy snails.

name: Ice Cream Plushie
description: Ice cream that will never melt in your hand. The downside? It's just a plushie.

name: Donut Slime
description: This slime is perfectly content as long as it has its precious donut. It will even hang out as furniture... just don't touch the donut.

name: Scuzzy Plushie
description: It's a teddy bear version of Scuzzy! A fuzzy Scuzzy, if you will.

name: Cute Monster Plushie
description: Definitely not a monster of the ferocious type, this cute plushie looks like it'd much rather make friends than scare people.

name: Double Headed Cat Plushie
description: Two heads just means this plushie will have to get twice the ear scratchies.

name: Bee Plushie
description: A soft bumble bee plushie, just as cute as the real thing and significantly less likely to sting when you hug it.

name: Ghost Plushie
description: This plushie holds its ghostly little arms out as if to frighten you, though it really it just looks like it's asking for a hug.

name: Candy Plushie
description: Candy is dandy and plushies are... well, nothing cute rhymes with 'plushie', but the point is that this candy plushie is a real treat.

name: Spider Plushie
description: Eight legs of pure plushie adorableness, how can even the most serious spider-hater say no to this cute little guy?

name: Mystic Orb
description: Warning: Orb may cause spontanious bouts of pondering.

name: Squid Plushie
description: Squid are at home in the dark depths of the deep ocean. This little plushie squid, on the other hand, would be most at home on your couch.

name: Bat Tea Set
description: The kettle and cups are made of black porcelain clay, collected from the marshlands around Withergate. The bat is just along for the ride.

name: Spiderweb Painting
description: A web of spider silk, depicted as a painting. Very goth, very spider.

name: Cauldron
description: The contents of this bubbling cauldron is unknown, but you can bet every last one of your tickets that it is most assuredly of the wicked variety.

name: Bat Window
description: Found yourself stuck choosing between getting a window or getting bats? Why not get BOTH? You deserve it.

name: Bat Monster Statue
description: A fiendishly chiseled statue of dark stone, the gemstone eyes almost seem to follow your every movement.

name: Moon Mirror
description: It isn't the easiest mirror to use, but why should functionality come before style?

name: Moon Banner
description: An ornate tapestry that beautifully depicts a starry night sky, it wouldn't look out of place even hanging in Withergate's castle.

name: Pumpkin Plushie
description: If this plushie ever got a hole in it, what would you patch it with? A PUMPKIN patch.

name: Bat Plushie
description: Small and fuzzy, this plushie could almost be mistaken for the real thing.

name: Candy Corn Plushie
description: This plushie might not be yummy like the real candy, but with his happy face and super soft stuffing, it's got a sweetness of its very own.

name: Shooting Star Plushie
description: Throw this plushie over your head and make a wish. It probably won't work, but it'll be cute.

name: Snaccoon Plushie
description: Fed plenty of wool stuffing, this chubby plushie is ready for a nice long nap at your place.

name: Sprinkles Plushie
description: A plushie modeled after the famous pet, now you can have TWICE the Sprinkles fun.

name: Charon Plushie
description: Withergate's trusty and ever-working boat-hound, now collectable in plushie form.

name: Slobert Plushie
description: Oh, a plushie of Slobert. And look, it's made out of slime. How wonderful.

name: Chubby Dynus Plushie
description: Can plushies be menacing? Dynus's plushie is here to say that yes, plushies CAN be menacing.

name: Withergate Fence
description: Metal fencing that is as durable as it is imposing. Any would-be invaders will think twice before stepping foot onto your farm.

name: Small Withergate Lamp
description: Demons in Withergate have perfected the art of glassblowing, allowing them to mass produce funky table lamps such as this.

name: Medium Withergate Lamp
description: A heavy bulb of glass blown from marsh sand. A sturdy iron pole keeps it hanging for a unique look.

name: Bent Withergate Lamp
description: The iron pole of this hanging lamp was accidentally bent during production, which just adds another dimension of style.

name: Large Withergate Lamp
description: Designed by Xyla herself as an original pitch for Withergate city streetlights, these didn't quite make the cut. The design has been repurposed into a line of floor lamps, like this one, however.

name: Squid Monster Statue
description: An ancient statue recovered from the Withergate swamps, it depicts a member of a primordial race that lived in the area long before the monsters came.

name: Jack'O'Rug
description: The grinning visage of a jack'o'lantern has been eternally captured in the fabric of this snazzy rug.

name: Nightsky Rug
description: Maybe you can't walk through the sky, but you can at least walk ON it with this plush purple rug.

name: Monster Fireplace
description: A great place to warm your feet... or your claws, or your tentacles, or your slime or... whatever else you like to warm.

name: Alien Plushie
description: Aliens may be out of this world, but this squishy plushie sure isn't. Pick him up today and take him to your leader.

name: Turtle Plushie
description: A squishy plushie turtle buddy, he could definitely get anyone to come out of their shell.

name: Fidget Spinner
description: Made of counterbalanced weights that keep spinning when given a flick. The citizens of Withergate are oddly divided on whether this toy is awesome or obnoxious.

name: Finger Traps
description: Brought to Withergate from a far away land, you'll never get them off your fingers by pulling them apart. The trick is to push your fingers together.

name: Puzzle Cube
description: A puzzle of colored tiles, you could spend hours trying to figure out the correct solution.

name: Piggy Bank
description: A clay piggy with a slot in his back for tickets, what a quaint little idea.

name: Fuzzy Dice
description: Feeling lucky? These fuzzy novelty dice quickly became a popular decoration in Withergate homes, though no one is quite sure why.

name: Tailor Store Model
description: A model replica created by Xyla of the Withergate tailor shop. Does it come with a little model Arianella, too?

name: Pool Table
description: A game of Demon invention, players use sticks to knock balls into holes. The clack of the marble balls striking one another is almost iconic in itself.

name: Plain Pumpkin
description: Fresh from the patch and ready for any and all forms of pumpkin-related shenanigans.

name: Witch Pumpkin
description: Which pumpkin is the witch pumpkin? Oh, it's the one with the witch's hat! Obviously.

name: Monstrous Pumpkin
description: Someone went the extra mile to make this grinning jack-o-lantern look especially fiendish!

name: Pumpkin Carriage
description: Yes, this is a carriage made out of a giant hollowed out pumpkin. To an outsider it might seem strange, but to Withergate's nobility this is a first class ride.
